51.0	Sherry_Turkle	Sherry Turkle	Sherry Turkle is a Professor of the Social Studies of Science and Technology at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. Obtaining her undergraduate degree of BA of Social Studies and later her Ph.D. in Sociology and Personality Psychology at Harvard University, she now focuses her research on psychoanalysis and human-technology interaction. She has written several books focusing on the psychology of human relationships with technology, especially in the realm of how people relate to computational objects.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Sherry_Turkle.jpg/220px-Sherry_Turkle.jpg
